    "actions_taken": [
      "All stop given immediately",
      "Personnel attended to injured derrickman",
      "Injured worker taken to Rig Medic",
      "Helicopter evacuation for medical evaluation",
      "BSEE Lafayette District investigation performed",
      "Documents, photographs, and witness statements obtained"
    ],
    "summary": "On 25 June 2018 at 05:30 hours, a Noble Derrickman sustained a foot injury when a 2-inch chiksan line assembly fell approximately 36 inches from an aft 5-ton air hoist (tugger) while being lifted at the auxiliary floor area of the Noble Don Taylor drill ship. The assembly struck the top of the derrickman's right foot, resulting in three fractures. The worker was evacuated by helicopter for medical evaluation and was not cleared to return to offshore work.",
    "recommendations": [
      "BSEE Lafayette District recommended issuing a Safety Alert for this incident"
    ],
